Bob, this might be related: IE 8: JS call to new Image() fails when the code is run in a popup window Is the quiz being displayed in a popup window? I think the line of code that is causing you problems is in the following function: 
```text
function PreloadImages(){


    var a = PreloadImages.arguments;


    for (var i=0; i<a.length; i++){


        Imgs[i] = new Image();


        Imgs[i].src = a[i];


    }


}
```
 Which for reference comes from hp6utilities.js_. You could try changing the fourth line to: `Imgs[i] = (window.Image ? new Image() : document.createElement('img'));` Try the above modification and let me know how you get on. And please send over the html file if you have a minute. thanks Gordon

