Hi Suzanna, I took a closer look at the JavaScript code in that HTML file you sent and it turned out not to be so scary. The documentation about this effect is here: http://www.dynamicdrive.com/dynamicindex17/ddaccordion.htm The "onopenclose" section looked interesting, so I went here: http://www.dynamicdrive.com/dynamicindex17/ddaccordion_suppliment2.htm The important information is in the section entitled "The onopenclose(...) event". Using that as my guide, I found that your JQuiz can work in Moodle with the folowing change: open the HTML file with your favorite text editor locate the line containing the "onopenclose:function" (around line 2153) replace the "// do nothing" line with the following code: 
```text
if (state=="block" && isclicked==true){


 if (window.StretchCanvasToCoverContent) {


  StretchCanvasToCoverContent();


 }


}
```
 save the modified file and upload it Moodle For reference, I have attached a copy of your original HTML file that has been modified in the way described above. Please try that out and let me know what happens. regards Gordon

For JCloze, the following should work: if you are distributing your Hot Potatoes quizzes with the HotPot module, you will need to add the following Javascript function to your page (skip this step if you are using QuizPort): 
```text
function getOffset(obj, type){


 if (! obj){


 return 0;


 }


 switch (type){


 case 'Width':


 case 'Height':


 return eval('(obj.offset'+type+'||0)');


 case 'Top':


 case 'Left':


 return eval('(obj.offset'+type+'||0) + getOffset(obj.offsetParent, type)');


 case 'Right':


 return getOffset(obj, 'Left') + getOffset(obj, 'Width');


 case 'Bottom':


 return getOffset(obj, 'Top') + getOffset(obj, 'Height');


 default:


 return 0;


 }


}
```
 within the ShowMessage function, locate the following line: `FDiv.style.display = 'block';` insert the following code *after* the above line: 
```text
 var FButton = document.getElementById('FeedbackOKButton');


 var CButton = document.getElementById('CheckButton2');


 if (FButton && CButton) {


 FDiv.style.top = (getOffset(FDiv, 'Top') + getOffset(CButton, 'Top') - getOffset(FButton, 'Top')) + 'px';


 FDiv.style.left = (getOffset(FDiv, 'Left') + getOffset(CButton, 'Left') - getOffset(FButton, 'Left') + 10) + 'px';


 }
```
 You may have to change the id of the CButton element depending on the Hot Potatoes quiz type and other customizations you may have made. all the best Gordon
